<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" leftmargin="0" topmargin="0">
While their stubby fingers may not seem suited to dainty stitchery, iksar (possibly in fear of the wrath of iksar necromancers) have learned how to fashion six unique robes. While the final combine for these robes must be performed by an iksar, the subcombines are not race-restricted, and the robes can be worn by any INT caster, regardless of race.<p>
Iksar tailors recieve their no drop Cabilisan robe patterns from Pagnar Vyng in East Cabilis (980, -300) by telling him "I need a robe pattern".<p><br><div align="right">Last Modified By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-05-26 07:00:01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
